    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>Biome: Other<br><span style=\"color:#f00;\">Exceedingly Rare</span></em></p>\n<p>A secret guarded closely by ancient sects of druids around the realm, vortax is a green powder made from a plant of the same name. This powder must be held in the hand of a druid and burned, causing [[/roll 3d8]] fire damage to the druid, making druids that constantly use vortax easy to pick out. After the vortax is burned away, the druid&rsquo;s hands will start to glow a faint green. The druid can, as an action, conjure up a powerful thunderstorm within a mile radius area, and command any target to be struck by [[/roll 5d20]] lightning damage with no saving throws. This effect lasts for [[/roll 1d4]] minutes.</p>",
